 nickname for a thin or rigid-looking person, from <i>bastone</i> ‘stick’.","English (Devon): variant of   Baston  ."]},{"name":"Baton","meanings":["French (<b>Bâton</b>): nickname from <i>bâton</i> (Old French <i>bastun</i>) ‘stick’; see   Baston   1.","English and Scottish: variant of   Batten  .","History: This surname (see 1 above) is listed in the register of Huguenot ancestors recognized by the Huguenot Society of America."]}]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705201,"age":67,"year":"1549","julianDay":2286821,"title":"Book of Common Prayer","description":"Book of Common Prayer, a product of the English Reformation, was published in 1549 for assistance in the administration of the sacraments and other rites and ceremonies of the church according to the use of the Church of England. The book outlined morning, evening, and communion prayers and orders for baptism and marriage, thus making England a truly Protestant state.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Book_of_Common_Prayer","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Book of Common Prayer","jurisdictionLevel":1},{"id":1705202,"age":76,"year":"1558","julianDay":2290108,"title":"Act of Uniformity","description":"The Act of Uniformity was passed by the Parliament of England and required all people to go to church once a week. The consequence of not attending church was a fine of 12 pence, which was a considerable amount for a poor person.","jurisdictionLevel":1},{"id":1705207,"age":103,"year":"1585","julianDay":2299970,"title":"The First English Colony is Established in America","description":"England established its first colony in North America in 1585 as a way to generate additional wealth. The colony was named Virginia, after the virgin Queen Elizabeth I.","jurisdictionLevel":1},{"id":1705208,"age":105,"year":"1587","julianDay":2300700,"title":"Elizabeth I Signs Death Warrant for Mary, Queen of Scots","description":"Elizabeth I signed the death warrant for Mary, Queen of Scots, on February 1, 1587, as she was found guilty of plotting to assasinate Elizabeth. Mary, Queen of Scots, was beheaded at Fotheringhay Castle in England on February 8, 1587.","url":"https://www.elizabethi.org/mary_queen_of_scots/","urlTitle":"Elizabeth I.org - Mary Queen of Scots","jurisdictionLevel":1}],"lifeSummary":"Baston was born in 1482, in Dorset, England. She married John Howchyns in 1505, in Broadwindsor, Dorset, England. They were the parents of at least 2 sons and 1 daughter."},"et":{"1482–":"1482–Surnud","1486–1539":"1486–1539","1505–1569":"1505–1569","1510–1557":"1510–1557","1511–Male":"1511–Surnud","1482–Female":"1482–Surnud","11 January 1505":"11. jaanuar 1505","1482":"1482","1558":"1558","1569":"1569","1557":"1557","1511":"1511","1510":"1510","1587":"1587","1585":"1585","1486":"1486","1539":"1539","1505":"1505","1549":"1549","Broadwinsor Liberty, Dorset, England, United Kingdom":"Broadwinsor Liberty, Dorset, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Broadwindsor, Dorset, England":"Broadwindsor, Dorset, England","Broadwindsor, Dorset, England, United Kingdom":"Broadwindsor, Dorset, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Dorset, England":"Dorset, England"},"fi":{"1482–":"1482–Kuollut","1486–1539":"1486–1539","1505–1569":"1505–1569","1510–1557":"1510–1557","1511–Male":"1511–Kuollut","1482–Female":"1482–Kuollut","11 January 1505":"11. tammikuuta 1505","1482":"1482","1558":"1558","1569":"1569","1557":"1557","1511":"1511","1510":"1510","1587":"1587","1585":"1585","1486":"1486","1539":"1539","1505":"1505","1549":"1549","Broadwinsor Liberty, Dorset, England, United Kingdom":"Broadwinsor Liberty, Dorset, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Broadwindsor, Dorset, England":"Broadwindsor, Dorset, England","Broadwindsor, Dorset, England, United Kingdom":"Broadwindsor, Dorset, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Dorset, England":"Dorset, England"},"fr":{"1482–":"1482–Décédée","1486–1539":"1486–1539","1505–1569":"1505–1569","1510–1557":"1510–1557","1511–Male":"1511–Décédé","1482–Female":"1482–Décédée","11 January 1505":"11 janvier 1505","1482